entry.title: Untitled
entry.summary: After a series of appeals, Jon Gruden's lawsuit against the NFL appears set for a public trial. On Thursday, the Nevada Supreme Court rejected the NFL's petition to rehear a recent decision on the case with a 7-0 vote, via ESPN's Don Van Natta Jr. It's the latest legal win for the former head coach as he tries to keep the proceedings from happening behind closed doors. In August, the court sided with Gruden in an appeal that blocked the NFL from sending the case into closed-door arbitration.
